item.title: Janusz add a quote by Gabriel García Márquez
item.description: "The world must be all fucked up," he said then, "when men travel first class and literature goes as freight." -- Gabriel García Márquez

item.title: Janusz add a quote by Matt Groening
item.description: "Love is a snowmobile racing across the tundra and then suddenly it flips over, pinning you underneath. At night, the ice weasels come." -- Matt Groening

item.title: Janusz add a quote by Jhonen Vasquez
item.description: "The numbing mind-ream of knowing you're alone not because people won't accept you but because you find so little worth accepting. An imposed solitude is better than simply tolerating your company in waiting for something better. So loneliness is not such a terrible thing when you consider that the alternative to thought provoking solace is to be surrounded only by remindings of why that solitude is preferable." -- Jhonen Vasquez

item.title: Janusz add a quote by Brené Brown
item.description: "We cannot selectively numb emotions, when we numb the painful emotions, we also numb the positive emotions." -- Brené Brown
